Introduction

Nam Woo Hyun is a South Korean singer and actor currently under BILLIONS and Jflex. He is best known as a member of the boy group INFINITE and was formerly part of the project unit Toheart. As a solo artist, he promotes under his full name and made his official solo debut on May 9, 2016, with the mini-album, "Write...".

He began his career in the entertainment industry with his debut as a member of INFINITE on June 9, 2010, through the release of the group’s first mini-album, First Invasion. Over the years, he has gained recognition for his powerful vocals, emotional performances, and active participation in composing and producing music.

After 14 years with Woollim Entertainment, Woo Hyun decided not to renew his contract, officially parting ways with the company on October 7, 2022. Despite his departure, he continues to be an active member of INFINITE. On March 20, 2023, he signed an exclusive contract with Jflex Entertainment to further his career as both a singer and actor.
Regarding his military service, Woo Hyun enlisted as a public service worker on October 24, 2019, instead of serving as an active duty soldier due to a significant shoulder injury he sustained in 2014. He successfully completed his service and was discharged on August 4, 2021.
